result.execSummary:
The defendant Racheal N Germain was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Habitual Criminality], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Possession of THC [Modifiers: Repeater], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Racheal N Germain not in court.  ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.

ADA Shock notes that Dodge County open case show the same Tweedy Street address, but then there is also a PO Box address in Oconomowoc. ADA Shock indicates that CCAP records show that the Dodge County Court authorized issuance of a warrant in a case yesterday.

The Court discloses that in the Court's former capacity as Jefferson County District Attorney, attorneys that DA Wambach supervised did prosecute Ms. Germain. The Court does not feel that any disqualification or recusal is needed.
